OASISFormat: 0.3
Name: uutf
Version: 0.9.0
Synopsis: Non-blocking streaming Unicode codec for OCaml
Authors: Daniel Bünzli <daniel.buenzli at erratique.ch>
Copyrights: (c) 2012 Daniel C. Bünzli
License: BSD3
Homepage: http://erratique.ch/software/uutf
Description:
 Uutf is a non-blocking streaming codec to decode and encode the UTF-8,
 UTF-16, UTF-16LE and UTF-16BE encoding schemes. It can efficiently
 work character by character without blocking on IO. Decoders perform 
 character position tracking and support newline normalization. 
 .
 Functions are also provided to fold over the characters of UTF encoded
 OCaml string values and to directly encode characters in OCaml Buffer.t
 values.
 .
 Uutf is made of a single, independent, module and distributed under
 the BSD3 license.

